<br>
If you swim in circles where power is the major determining factor (Oh!  You are level 57?  Okay, come on our raid.  What's your name again?) you aer going to encounter this problem a lot more than others.  If you priortize friendships, mutual support, and activities with your established friends, you are *far* less likely to ever come into direct contact with a problem like this.  I'm not directly condeming one play mindset over another, just pointing out that you get what you are looking for.  That goes for RL also, btw, but I'll refrain from drawing the moral examples.<br>
<br>
I have the blessing to be in a guild that's held together into the early 50s now (maybe a dozen of us there now, with another dozen on the way) and I'm confident that we will hold together far longer.  I don't think I'll ever need to worry about seeing an E-Baby with my guildtag on.  We have allies, and the same goes for them.  Not trying to boast, just showing that the best way to avoid this problem is to not set your priorities in line with those who will go looking for the quick fix.<br>
<br>
Anyway, there's my 2 coppers again.<br>
<br>
