<br>
In my humble opinion, money in the real world should be kept out of the game as much as possible.<br>
<br>
I was playing EQ back when Ebaying was an easy option, back before the dupe bug was fixed. I had friends who were making over $2,000 a month duping and/or harvesting items for Ebay. It mauled the economy of the server I was on at the time and really messed up the game dynamics of the server to this day.<br>
<br>
Any game is designed with a balance of power in mind. In Risk, you need to do certain things before you amass the power to take over the world. In Monopoly, you need a certain amount of property and cash.<br>
<br>
EQ was designed with a power balance between players and mobs in mind. Ebaying, harvesting, duping, and any of the other activities that artificially affect the economy and power balance of a server can have a significant affect on the game as a whole for everyone... <br>
<br>
I could go into the details of this, but it would make for a long, long post, so I wont. It suffices to say that I was, and still am, glad that Verrant has worked to keep the game and the economies of the servers as free from the influence of money in the real world as possible. <br>
<br>
I hope it continues, although it wouldnt surprise me if Verrant tried to work out a way of allowing it at some point, with a fee being paid to them. Its all about $$$, after all.<br>
